                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18293</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from"
                            >Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-01T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. In reply to Department’s 111. Note which am informed officially represents
                    attitude General Carranza and Cabinet, radically different in tone and style
                    from general tenor as outlined previously to me by Secretary of State for
                    Foreign Affairs. Foreign Office today asserted to me that note represented exact
                    sentiment and determination of Mexican authorities.</p>
                <p>Note published here last evening. Conservative foreign opinion that it is
                    aggressive, is inaccurate, indecorous and inopportune. Radical opinion that it
                    is inexact, improper and impudent. Generally considered as further extending
                    difficulties which are perplexing and dangerous enough without adding
                    international complications. However <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government
                    authorities appear well satisfied with note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
